OL,3,CNewborns with jaundice treated at home
OL,4,Cin sleeping bag-style garment
OL,6,FNewborn babies with jaundice can now
OL,7,Fbe treated at home in a special
OL,8,Fsleeping bag-style garment following
OL,9,Fthe launch of a Hospital at Home
OL,10,Fservice by Scotland's biggest health
OL,11,Fboard.
OL,13,FThe service enables babies who meet
OL,14,Fthe clinical criteria to receive
OL,15,Fphototherapy using the garment, which
OL,16,Femits therapeutic light.
OL,18,FAround six in 10 newborns are affected
OL,19,Fby neonatal jaundice and they often
OL,20,Fneed several days of phototherapy
OL,21,Ftreatment.
