OL,3,CNewborns with jaundice treated at home
OL,4,Cin sleeping bag-style garment
OL,6,FTraditionally mothers and babies would
OL,7,Fneed to return to hospital for
OL,8,Ftreatment, which can be disruptive
OL,9,Fwhen they are just settling into a
OL,10,Froutine at home.
OL,12,FThe Hospital at Home service launched
OL,13,Fby the neonatal unit at the Royal
OL,14,FHospital for Children in Glasgow means
OL,15,Fbabies can now be treated safely and
OL,16,Fcomfortably in their own surroundings.
