OL,6,FAs part of the service, a neonatal
OL,7,Fsenior nurse visits each family at
OL,8,Fhome every day to check the baby's
OL,9,Fbilirubin levels, assess progress, and
OL,10,Fdetermine whether treatment should
OL,11,Fcontinue.
OL,13,FIf the families have any questions at
OL,14,Fother times, someone is available over
OL,15,Fthe phone.
OL,17,FThe service started work on November
OL,18,F24 last year and as of January 8, 40
OL,19,Fhave received jaundice treatment at
OL,20,Fhome.
